<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,189,215]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[324,634,189,215]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenoderma">
<emphasis box="[324,634,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hydrodroma amoenoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has many features in common with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walter, 1908)" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1040,1375,189,215]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torrenticola">
<emphasis box="[1040,1207,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. torrenticola</emphasis>
(Walter, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
from the northern hemisphere: (1) Integument papillae of two 
<typeStatus box="[774,836,225,251]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">types</typeStatus>
, larger ones (with rounded tips) surrounded by smaller ones arranged in a hexagonal pattern; (2) Cx-I with a smooth medial margin; (3) swimming setation well developed (on IV-L-5 on both surfaces), but posterior surfaces of II-L-5 bearing only one, of IV-L-5 less than 10 swimming setae; (4) claws moderately developed (8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[614,628,333,359]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
14 % L penultimate segment). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[976,1259,333,359]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torrenticola">
<emphasis box="[976,1259,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hydrodroma torrenticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenoderma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. amoenoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in (1) a weaker development of the hexagonal smaller integument papillae (developed as flattened projections, not reaching 50% H of main papillae); (2) a more slender chelicera (total L/H&gt; 5.3); (3) a stouter P-4 (variability with a slight overlap, L/H 4.1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,638,441,467]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
4.6); (4) lower numbers of swimming setae on III-L (n posterior setae III-L-4, 
<specimenCount box="[244,286,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
8, 
<specimenCount box="[323,365,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[387,401,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
9, III-L-5, 
<specimenCount box="[523,565,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,601,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
7, 
<specimenCount box="[631,674,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
, 4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[702,716,477,503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
6). A further difference concerns the genital field: In contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,345,513,539]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoenoderma">
<emphasis box="[151,345,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. amoenoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, no distinct sexual dimorphism is found in number and density of medial genital plate setae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1908" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torrenticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">H. torrenticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<specimenCount box="[300,346,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
: 32 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[385,399,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
53, ratio setae number/plate L 0.13 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,803,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.20, 
<specimenCount box="[866,910,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
: 25 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[951,965,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
40, ratio 0.11 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1113,1127,549,575]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">–</emphasis>
0.16).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,683]" box="[199,941,584,611]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,584,611]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Habitat:</emphasis>
Pools of streams, mostly in open, unforested landscapes.
</paragraph>
